Environmental Engineer 1 (May '20 Grads)

CDM Smith

- Kansas City, MO

Looking for an eager new graduate interested in remediation sites and feasibility studies, cost estimating, EPA Superfund interest, solid waste facilities, etc. Reviews draft designs and reports for compliance with federal, state and local regulations. Ensures that firm policies and practices are followed on all designs. Performs site reviews and studies, as needed, to ensure designs are aligned with location specifications. Updates design requirements as necessary. Performs water quality analyses and modeling. Contributes to firm's TKM by developing white papers and technical design documentation of new or special case designs, studies, etc. Submits technical papers and designs for publishing to technical journals. May create or work with a team to create a poster or other presentation material for a conference. Performs other duties as required.
Minimum Qualifications
Education: Bachelor's degree in civil, environmental or chemical engineering or related discipline. Experience: 0 years. Travel: Domestic and/or international travel may be required. The frequency of travel is contingent on specific duties, responsibilities, and the essential functions of the position, which may vary depending on workload and project demands.

